# Member auth terminology

BamSignal **member login** is **username + 6-digit PIN**, not email/password.

## UI copy (member AuthPage)

- Login fields: **Username**, **PIN**
- Link: **Forgot PIN?** — not "Forgot password?"
- Errors/messages: "Invalid username or PIN", "Enter your PIN" — not password wording
- Signup still collects email for verification; login screen does not present email/password auth

## Do not break

- Login PIN on `AuthPage` uses `showToggle={false}` so centered text aligns with username (no eye icon offset)
- Internal state/API may still use `password` for Supabase — that is backend only; user-facing text stays PIN/username
- Admin auth (`AdminAuthPage`) is separate — email/password is correct there

## Login field layout

- Both login fields use `auth-field--centered auth-field--login`
- PIN uses `auth-pin-input` with same horizontal padding as username (18px), `text-align: center`
